    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-01T11:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-01T11:36:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/343</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Port Limon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port Limon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-01T11:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cable February 28, 6 p.m. Revolution apparently over, failure due chiefly to
                    fact Government had practically all ammunition and guns in the country.
                    Responsibility for firing on passenger train being investigated according to the
                    Governor Limon but believe nothing will really be done without demand of our
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
